# Introduction to Classic Load Balancers

## Cloud Service Provider
* Amazon Web Services (AWS)

## Difficulty
Introductory

## Scenario
Demonstrate using Classic Load Balancers by distributing traffic between 2-3 different EC2 instances.
  1. Configure an Ec2 instance that has an Apache HTTP server installed on it -- to display a simple webpage.
  2. Create Security Group for your instance.
  3. Create a CLB.
  4. Edit inbound rules for Security Groups.
  5. Test CLB.

